The Zondo Commission has heard that former police minister Nkosinathi Nhleko, who appointed a convicted felon as his chief of staff, was not aware of the conviction when he hired Leon Mbangwa. Nhleko was testifying before the state capture commission on Monday after he had been implicated by several people, including the former head of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate, Robert McBride. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will continue to hear testimony from former Police Minister Nathi Nhleko on Tuesday. The commission is hearing evidence relating to allegations of corruption at the law enforcement agencies. WATCH: Former police minister Nathi Nhleko testifies at state capture inquiry Colonel Nyameko Xaba is also expected to testify at the commission.